M|references|**Structure:** Current reality → Complicating challenge → Question that speaks to need → Optional answer.
M|references|**Best for:** Consultative selling. Mirrors how professionals present to leadership.
M|references|> Your team doubled this year. That usually means onboarding is eating into selling time. How are you handling ramp for new hires?
M|references|**Structure:** Contrarian hook → Explain benefit simply → Provide proof → Strong CTA.
M|references|**Best for:** Analytical buyers who need evidence (engineers, CFOs, ops leaders).
M|references|> Most sales teams measure rep activity. The top 5% measure rep efficiency instead. When Acme switched, they booked 40% more meetings with fewer emails. Worth seeing how?
M|references|**Structure:** Compliment → Case Study → CTA.
M|references|**Best for:** Agency/services cold outreach. Case study does the heavy lifting.
M|references|> Big fan of [Company]. We just built an app for [cp] that does XYZ. I have a few more ideas. Interested?
M|references|**Structure:** Observation + Binary value-prop question. 1–2 sentences total.
M|references|**Best for:** Maximum brevity. Impulsive reply based on curiosity.
M|references|> Looks like you're hiring reps. Would it be helpful to get a more granular look at how they're ramping on email?
M|references|**Structure:** Trigger/Pain → Solution hint → Binary CTA. 1–3 sentences, no intro.
M|references|**Best for:** High-velocity SDR teams. Mobile-optimized. Deliberately polarizing.
M|references|Spend max 1 minute on personalization. Use industry/persona-level signals. For top-tier prospects, quote their own words from interviews — they almost always respond.
M|references|**Structure:** Observation → Problem/Insight → Credibility → Solution → Call-to-Conversation.
M|references|**Best for:** Universal "base" framework that works everywhere. Five parts.
M|references|**Structure:** Problem → Amplify → Story → Testimony → Offer → rsp.
M|references|**Best for:** Longer-form or multi-email sequences. Consulting, education, complex B2B services. Each element can be developed across separate touches.